      </sec>
      <sec id="article-35895.s9" sec-type="Prognosis">
        <title>Prognosis</title>
        <p>The prognosis of these patients is largely based on the severity of the injuries. Since many patients with maxillary sinus fractures will also have multiple other injuries, it is difficult to predict outcomes. Some negative prognostic indicators include anosmia, complete vision loss, severe fracture displacement, and late intervention; however, patients with these symptoms likely have more severe injuries than an isolated maxillary sinus fracture.<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="article-35895.r1">[1]</xref> The most common long-term complication is dental malocclusion or malunion of the fracture site.<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="article-35895.r7">[7]</xref></p>
      </sec>
